syntax.model:
ind60 =~ JaspColumn_9_Encoded + JaspColumn_10_Encoded + JaspColumn_11_Encoded
  dem60 =~ JaspColumn_1_Encoded + JaspColumn_2_Encoded + JaspColumn_3_Encoded + JaspColumn_4_Encoded
  dem65 =~ JaspColumn_5_Encoded + JaspColumn_6_Encoded + JaspColumn_7_Encoded + JaspColumn_8_Encoded

  dem60 ~ ind60
  dem65 ~ ind60 + dem60

  JaspColumn_1_Encoded ~~ JaspColumn_5_Encoded
  JaspColumn_2_Encoded ~~ JaspColumn_4_Encoded + JaspColumn_6_Encoded
  JaspColumn_3_Encoded ~~ JaspColumn_7_Encoded
  JaspColumn_4_Encoded ~~ JaspColumn_8_Encoded
  JaspColumn_6_Encoded ~~ JaspColumn_8_Encoded
syntax.modelOriginal:
# measurement model
  ind60 =~ x1 + x2 + x3
  dem60 =~ y1 + y2 + y3 + y4
  dem65 =~ y5 + y6 + y7 + y8
# regressions
  dem60 ~ ind60
  dem65 ~ ind60 + dem60
# residual correlations
  y1 ~~ y5
  y2 ~~ y4 + y6
  y3 ~~ y7
  y4 ~~ y8
  y6 ~~ y8

footnotes.text: Estimator is ML. Model test is standard.
